    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2005-05-12</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2005-06-06T19:32:57Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Rural Disaster Assistance Fairness Act of 2005 - Amends the Robert T. Stafford Disaster Relief and Emergency Assistance Act to require the President to designate a Small State Advocate within the Federal Emergency Management Agency to advocate for the fair treatment of rural communities in the provision of assistance under such Act.</p> <p>Requires the Under Secretary for Emergency Preparedness and Response of the Department of Homeland Security to report to specified congressional committees on the extent to which disaster declaration regulations: (1) meet the needs of States with populations of less than 1 million; and (2) comply with existing statutory restrictions on the use of arithmetic formulas and sliding scales based on income or population.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
